# CF Access Service Token for `wrangler dev --remote`
#
# `portal-api` is mounted on a zone route behind Cloudflare Access, so
# `wrangler dev --remote` cannot reach it using browser cookies alone.
# A service token lets wrangler (a non-interactive client) authenticate
# directly against the Access app.
#
# One-time setup:
#
# 1. Cloudflare dashboard → Zero Trust → Access → Service Auth → Service Tokens
# 2. Create Service Token → name it "wrangler local dev" (duration: whatever)
# 3. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret — they're shown ONCE on creation
# 4. Open the Access application that covers `portal.guoyuer.com/api/*`
#    (Zero Trust → Access → Applications → the portal-api app)
# 5. Edit the application → Policies tab → Add Policy
#      - Name:    "wrangler local dev"
#      - Action:  Service Auth
#      - Include: Service Token → pick the one you just created
# 6. Save.
#
# Then: copy this file to `worker/.env.access`, paste in your values, and
# run `bash worker/dev-remote.sh` (the launcher sources this file before
# invoking wrangler). `.env.access` is gitignored by the root `.env*` rule.

CLOUDFLARE_ACCESS_CLIENT_ID=
CLOUDFLARE_ACCESS_CLIENT_SECRET=
